28/12/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- The interior ministry announced on Tuesday (27 December) that the deadline for foreign immigrants in Greece to apply for new residence or work permits has been extended, from the end of December to the end of February. Applicants must present authorities a passport with a stamp proving they entered Greece at least a year ago, as well as a document showing tax registration and social security status. (Kathimerini - 28/12/05) 
